d real code in this repository later, prefer a\nseparate module or crate layered on top of `but-agentlog`.\n\n### Agent Handoff\n\nThe handoff feature is expected to live in the GitButler CLI, but it needs a\nseparate design pass before implementation.\n\nThe rough workflow is:\n\n1. a user asks an agent to catch up with a branch or project\n2. the agent uses a skill and/or `but` CLI subcommands to discover relevant\n   historical sessions\n3. the agent reads a bounded timeline or related-session window\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:37:16.894Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}